author: felicity
msg: bug 3553: if in report_safe mode, and rewrite_header was set, and the message didn't have that header to rewrite, report_safe would add it without a newline at the end, so we'd have multiple headers in one line.  Now, if the header doesn't exist in the original, assume it was blank (just a newline) so the output ends up correct.

author: felicity
msg: bug 3582: Exim can put the port numbers in the Received header if port number logging is enabled.  Update the Received-header parsing to take the port numbers into account.
